column36: I struggled with an eating disorder and chronic pain issues my freshman year. I was treated without any dignity or compassion by faculty members, and eventually it led to me leaving school for 3 years. I had a particularly traumatic experience with Todd Adams where he and his colleagues first demanded I see certain practitioners (that my parents had to pay for with their own money), and then made certain oddly specific demands of what I needed to do to be "allowed" to stay on campus. Both my parents and personal doctors sent multiple letters, and had multiple meetings, asking the school to please let me and my personal Doctors deal with these issues without school involvement, but they refused. This eventually led to me having to take a forced leave of absence because they threatened if I didn't meet, again, certain oddly specific demands, that they would suspend me and my parents would lose the tuition for that quarter that they'd already paid. I was extremely traumatized by the whole experience and was treated in an extremely inhuman and cruel way. It ruined my college experience and though I'm now back and graduating soon, my experience here was forever tainted by the cold and insensitive way I was treated my freshman year.

column45: Lack of financial support if my MLOA was approved,Other
column46: I would lose my housing, so I wouldn't have had the adequate resources to get help for my mental health and it would've negatively impacted me. My professors were very accommodating, which was nice. However, I did feel trapped. I've read that some people who take MLOA's have trouble getting readmitted, and I was also scared about how it would impact my financial aid in the future because of the 4 year limit (although I did not look into this so maybe this wasn't an issue). My therapist had really really wanted me to go to an all day program while still living in the dorms, so that I could go to one up here since there’s none close to my hometown, but I would've gotten kicked out with nowhere to go and no way to pay my rent so I just struggled through the end of the quarter.
